A small number of players may experience epileptic seizures when exposed to flashing lights or visual patterns in video games.

Certain conditions may also trigger epileptic symptoms in individuals with no prior history of seizures. If you or a family member has a history of seizures or epilepsy, consult a physician before playing. If you experience eye discomfort, altered vision, headache, migraine, muscle twitching, convulsions, blackouts, loss of awareness, or disorientation while playing, stop IMMEDIATELY and seek medical advice before resuming play.

In addition, if you experience dizziness, nausea, symptoms similar to motion sickness, or any discomfort or pain in any part of your body while playing, IMMEDIATELY stop playing. If the condition persists, seek medical attention.

1. Items or furniture already placed in the Blueprint can be picked up and moved around as a group after you put the Blueprint away.
\n2. Only items you've placed and plants or crops you've grown yourself will be put away with the Blueprint. Naturally grown trees, flowers, and grass, as well as built houses, Luca Fruit, and other similar objects cannot be put away, moved, or placed with the Blueprint.
\n3. After putting the Blueprint away, it can be viewed in your Backpack and placed again.

1. Today's Greenmarket is a crop trading hub <style=ItemHighlight>formed by multiple planets</style>. Each planet may be assigned to a different <style=ItemHighlight>random market</style>.

2. Glenn purchases crops daily at the prices of the market your planet <style=ItemHighlight>currently</style> belongs to, and the list of accepted crops is updated regularly.

3. Daily purchase prices are determined by the <style=ItemHighlight>previous day's market supply</style>. When a crop <style=ItemHighlight>had low supply</style> the previous day, its <style=ItemHighlight>purchase price will be higher</style>, and vice versa.

4. At <style=ItemHighlight>04:00</style> each day, crop prices are updated based on the <style=ItemHighlight>total yield of all mature crops</style> from planets within the same market.

5. At <style=ItemHighlight>12:00</style> and <style=ItemHighlight>20:00</style> each day, the <style=ItemHighlight>latest farm data</style> for the listed crops in the current market is updated. This data can be used to <style=ItemHighlight>forecast</style> the next day's supply and prices.

6. The Message Board displays messages on prices and market demand from different random markets. Since purchased <style=ItemHighlight>crops and market prices</style> may vary, be sure to check the Message Board regularly.
